importFile

DESModel importFile(java.io.File src,
                    java.lang.String description)
                    throws java.io.IOException
Import a model. The format of the file is assumed to be given in the description. In order to access the list of supported formats, call IOPluginManager.getImporters().

Parameters:
src - the file to be imported
description - the description of the file format
Returns:
the imported model
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if there is a problem while importing the model
See Also:
IOPluginManager.getImporters(), ImportExportPlugin.getFileDescription(), FileLoadException

            java.io.File dst,
            java.lang.String description)
            throws java.io.IOException

Parameters:
model - the model to be exported
dst - the file where the exported model should be saved
description - the description of the file format
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if there is a problem while exporting the model
See Also:

getFileOfModel

java.io.File getFileOfModel(DESModel model)
Determine the file, if any, where the given model is saved.

Parameters:
model - the model
Returns:
the file where the given model is saved; null if the model has not been saved in a file yet

setFileOfModel

void setFileOfModel(DESModel model,
                    java.io.File file)
Specify the file where a model is saved. The file can be null.

This method simply sets an annotation. This method does not cause the model to be saved. To save a model, use save(DESModel, File).

Parameters:
model - the model
file - the file where the model is saved
